<div style="text-align: center;">
<div class="kauer-block" style="display: inline-block; text-align: center; font-family: arial; width: 75%; color: rgb(0, 9, 26);">
<div class="kauer-block" style="border: 0px solid black; background: #f2f2f2; margin-bottom: 1rem; text-spacing: 1px;">
<div style="margin-bottom: 2rem;"></div>
[[File:Kauer Logo.png|center|400px|link=]]
<div style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;"></div></div>

<div class="kauer-logoblock" style="border: 0px solid black; background: #f2f2f2; margin-bottom: 1rem; text-spacing: 1px;">
<div style="text-align: center; border-left: 2px solid #132f6e; border-right: 2px solid #132f6e; margin: 0px 1rem;">
<div style="display: inline-block; width: 80%;">''"And as we dive farther into the Backrooms, we are met with bizarrity, treachery, and the incomprehensible face of what humanity created from its beliefs."''</div></div></div>

<div class="kauer-block" style="border: 0px solid black; background: #f2f2f2; margin-bottom: 1rem; text-spacing: 1px;">
<div style="font-size: 30px; letter-spacing: 1px; border-bottom: 2px solid rgb(20, 90, 245); margin-bottom: 6px; color: #132f6e; font-family: arial;">'''Overview'''</div>
<div style="margin-bottom: 1rem;"></div>

The '''Kauer Research Organization''' is a major multifaceted group purposed for documenting the Backrooms' bizarre aspects, primarily phenomena and anomalous objects. Stationed in multiple levels, the K.R.O. continues their research on the unknown, the infinity, and the enigmatic.

With strong bonds with other prominent groups—such as the [[M.E.G.|'''Major Exploration Group''']], the [[Backroom Colonists|'''Backroom Colonists''']], the [[Entity Research Committee|'''Entity Research Committee''']], and the [[Backrooms Wiki|'''Database''']]—Kauer pushes humanity forward into the ultimate frontier, the Backrooms.

The Kauer Research Organization is extremely strict concerning confidentiality, keeping virtually all their data classified from the public, save for one archived article, which remains freely viewable—[[The Kauer Thesis|'''The Kauer Thesis''']]. While the Database has some copies of Kauer's documents, all of them are protected by a password.<div style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"></div></div>

<div class="kauer-block" style="border: 0px solid black; background: #f2f2f2; margin-bottom: 1rem; text-spacing: 1px;">
<div style="font-size: 30px; letter-spacing: 1px; border-bottom: 2px solid rgb(20, 90, 245); margin-bottom: 6px; color: #132f6e; font-family: arial;">'''History'''</div>
<div style="margin-bottom: 1rem;"></div>
Founded in 1943 as the Kauer Alliance, the group's mission was to analyze and document level properties. With poor technology, their progress began relatively slow. Over time, the Alliance accumulated members, changed its governance form, and expanded its studies.

With the passing years, technological advancements allowed the Alliance to rise in power, resources, reputation, and presence. In 1983, the organization's name was changed to the Kauer Research Organization.

Given the recent burst of anomalous activity recorded throughout the Backrooms, Kauer's activity has increased exponentially and is seeking to form alliances with more powerful groups, specifically those capable of aiding the organization in researching.<div style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"></div></div>

<div class="kauer-block" style="border: 0px solid black; background: #f2f2f2; margin-bottom: 1rem; text-spacing: 1px;">
<div style="font-size: 30px; letter-spacing: 1px; border-bottom: 2px solid rgb(20, 90, 245); margin-bottom: 6px; color: #132f6e; font-family: arial;">'''Locations'''</div>
<div style="margin-bottom: 1rem;"></div>
Due to the diversity of anomalies that the Backrooms present, the Kauer Research Organization has numerous branches, divisions, and subdivisions, all dedicated to a purpose. Every Kauer base's location remains strictly classified.

Wanderers who unintentionally encounter Kauer bases will be promptly offered assistance and directions to the nearest outpost.<div style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"></div></div>
<div class="kauer-block" style="border: 0px solid black; background: #f2f2f2; margin-bottom: 1rem; text-spacing: 1px;">
<div style="font-size: 30px; letter-spacing: 1px; border-bottom: 2px solid rgb(20, 90, 245); margin-bottom: 6px; color: #132f6e; font-family: arial;">'''Alliances'''</div>
<div style="margin-bottom: 1rem;"></div>
<div class="meg-fandom-block" style="text-align: center; font-family: Arial;">
[[File:M.E.G without the text.png|150px|link=|center]]<div style="margin-bottom: 10px;"></div>
[[M.E.G.|<span style="color: #6c724c; font-size: 20px;">'''The Major Exploration Group'''</span>]]<div style="margin-bottom: 10px;"></div>
Ties between the K.R.O. and the M.E.G. were cemented in 1950 with the Treaty of Base Alpha. Since then, both groups have been assisting each other following [[Phenomenon 12|the Flicker]].<div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"></div>
</div>
<div class="backrooms-pioneers-block" style="text-align: center; font-family: Arial;">
[[File:The Backroom Colonists Logo.png|150px|link=|center]]<div style="margin-bottom: 10px;"></div>
[[Backroom Colonists|<span style="color: gold; font-size: 20px;">'''The Backroom Colonists'''</span>]]<div style="margin-bottom: 10px;"></div>
The Kauer-Colonist Alliance was officially acknowledged in the Treaty of Fikes. While the two groups share little similarities in their goals, they remain ready to aid each other.<div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"></div>
</div>
<div class="backrooms-pioneers-block" style="background: #e0daa7; border: 0.3rem solid #d5cf9f; text-align: center; font-family: Arial;">
[[File:Site-logo.png|150px|link=|center]]<div style="margin-bottom: 10px;"></div>
[[The Database|<span style="color: #a34428; font-size: 20px;">'''The Database'''</span>]]<div style="margin-bottom: 10px;"></div>
While no official document confirms the alliance between Kauer and the Database, the latter often provides Kauer with overviews of levels, entities, objects, and phenomena.<div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"></div>
</div></div>
